WE are in the month of love and the valentine spirit still in the air. Love will continue being the buzz word for the entire month of February. Speaking about love, people often claim that one can never choose who they fall in love. While this may be true, who we fall in love with tends to fit our various personal requirements and standards we uphold. From one’s mannerism, how they look to also their income bracket. All these form part of things we look at when we fall in love with someone. Speaking of income, if you are looking at falling for the right person based on their occupation, then 29-Secrets magazine has the perfect love classifieds for you. According to the publication, these are the best occupations to fall in love with or occupations that make the best lovers in a relationship: 1. Teachers A person who can teach has already shown that they’re smart, understanding, patient and nurturing. With the number of holidays they receive due to academic breaks, they also provide the ideal person for baecations. 2. Dentists They call them the cool doctors because most dentists have calm professional lives, with the occasional root canal the height of their professional excitement. You can be sure that they won’t be leaping out of bed to perform emergency surgery on the weekend, so its more time for love. 3. Novelist/Writer Creative, expressive and passionate, they are also sensitive and curious and typically makes their own hours, which leaves plenty of time for the both of you. 4. Engineers With an education that leaned heavily toward maths and science, these individuals are practical, reasonable, methodical and dedicated. All this makes for a perfect partner.